cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR

This paper deals with unintended bias in machine learning, specifically in text classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces new metrics for measuring unintended bias, which falls under the category of machine learning evaluation, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with issues of fairness, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper uses a large new test set, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
